The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, held a press briefing on June 9, 2010. During the briefing, Gibbs discussed a range of topics including the UN sanctions vote on Iran, BP's response to the oil spill in the Gulf of Mexico, and the President's upcoming trip to the Gulf Coast. Gibbs also fielded questions from reporters on various issues, such as the President's involvement in the response to the oil spill, the administration's views on BP's actions, and the President's meetings with foreign leaders.